{
  "texts": [
    "Only a handful of HVM silicon photonics products are shipping today, requiring the fab to timeshare the production with other processes, and adding another source of yield impact.",
    "The option to integrate the PIC with the EIC has been around since the first commercially successful silicon photonic product 1, 127, 129.",
    "Developing a monolithic EPIC process (Fig. 4e), starting with a CMOS (or BiCMOS) SOI process and optimizing it for photonic applications, has been demonstrated several times [130] [131] [132] successfully.",
    "From the perspective of commercialization and time-to-market, a monolithic EPIC often 'seems to' be the superior technology of choice (Table 4).",
    "High-speed circuits such as drivers and TIAs can be colocated next to modulators and PDs, reducing parasitics and power consumption 133."
  ]
}